    "body":  "**Description:**\n\nIntroduce a non-functional, clearly labeled prototype button for LinkedIn integration, demonstrating the future capability to pre-fill qualifications from a user\u0027s LinkedIn profile. This serves as both a forward-looking feature and a talking point during demos and outreach.\n\n**Why This Matters:**\n\nSignals roadmap readiness for ecosystem integration (LinkedIn, HRIS, LMS, etc.).\n\nHighlights IMQ\u0027s intent to reduce manual data entry by leveraging existing user data.\n\nEnhances AI-focused messaging without introducing technical complexity at MVP stage.\n\n**UI Behavior:**\nPlacement:\n\nOn the Upload Qualifications page.\n\nDirectly beneath the current upload CV section or next to “Upload another document” button.\n\nDesign:\n\nButton labeled:\n🧠 Import from LinkedIn (Coming Soon)\n\nOptional hover tooltip:\n“Pre-populate qualifications from your LinkedIn profile — future feature”\n\nOn Click:\n\nOpens a non-functional modal or toast notification stating:\n\n“This feature is not yet available in the prototype. In a future release, IMQ will support linking to your LinkedIn profile to intelligently extract qualifications.”\n\nVisibility:\n\nThis is demo-only; should not appear in production versions until full authentication, consent, and data parsing features are implemented.\n\n**Notes for Future Implementation (Reference Only):**\n\nOAuth-based authentication to access profile with user consent.\n\nNLP pipeline to extract experience, certifications, education, titles.\n\nAI validation to avoid importing outdated or unverifiable entries.",
